title: [react]: Remove deprecated+removed APIs
body:
React v16 [has removed APIs deprecated in 15.5](https://reactjs.org/blog/2017/09/26/react-v16.0.html#packaging):
- `React.PropTypes` -> `prop-types`
- `React.createClass` -> `create-react-class`
- `React.DOM` -> `react-dom-factories`

This PR adds definitions for `create-react-class` and `react-dom-factories` and removes the deprecated APIs from the `react` definitions (while preserving the relevant interfaces and tests in the `react` package).

This is a breaking change, but that change was made in React 16 so the typings were actually wrong in 16.0.0 and could lead to unexpected runtime errors.

Tests were updated for a number of affected packages.

Note that this revealed existing errors in `redux-form` with TypeScript@next and `strictFunctionTypes` enabled. Since I am not familiar with that library, I chose to disable that option for the time being. One of its authors should investigate.
